something like this will be needed for a self signed deployment option

Create the CA private key:
openssl genpkey -algorithm RSA -out ca-key.pem -pkeyopt rsa_keygen_bits:4096

Create the CA certificate:
openssl req -x509 -new -noenc -key ca-key.pem -sha256 -days 3650 -out ca-cert.pem -config ca.conf

Generate the Server Private Key
openssl genpkey -algorithm RSA -out server-key.pem -pkeyopt rsa_keygen_bits:4096

Create the Certificate Signing Request (CSR) for the Server
openssl req -new -key /etc/swanctl/private/server-key.pem -outform pem -out server-req.pem 

Create serial file???:
790D30588E77E68556A29927CF29AC3D0C1A2A11

Sign the CSR:
openssl ca -in server-req.pem -inform pem -config server.conf

